The paper deals with a distributed monitoring model for data streams, which involves algorithms for tracking the top-k positions of the observed values. This problem is related to data structures, distributed computing, information theory, and networking. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
